Company Overview

Logistics Plus® puts the 'plus' in logistics by doing both the big and little things needed to ensure our customers’ success.

Global Logistics
+ So Much More!

Logistics Plus, Inc. (LP) is a 21st Century Logistics Company™ and a global leader in transportation, warehousing, fulfillment, logistics, business intelligence, technology, and unique supply chain solutions.

Logistics Plus continues to adapt to a constantly changing world. We say “yes” by providing creative solutions to any supply chain challenge. Combining our passionate workforce with world-class technology, we are agile, innovative, clever, and resourceful.

Logistics Plus was founded by Jim Berlin in 1996 in Erie, Pennsylvania. Today, the company has annual global sales approaching $1 billion and over 1,200 employees in more than 50 countries worldwide.

The Logistics Plus® network:

The Logistics Plus® network includes offices or warehouses located in Erie, PA; Aurora, CO; Brea, CA; Buffalo, NY; Charlotte, NC; Chicago, IL; Chino, CA; Cleveland, OH; Colton, CA; Dallas, TX; Dayton, NJ; Haslet TX; Honolulu, HI; Houston, TX; Jamestown, NY; Kansas City, KS; Laredo, TX; Lexington, NC; Miami, FL; New York, NY; Norfolk, VA; Phoenix, AZ; Riverside, CA; Vancouver, WA; Wilmer, TX; Australia; Brazil; Canada; China; Colombia; Czech Republic; Denmark; Egypt; Germany; India; Indonesia; Ireland; Japan; Malaysia; Mexico; Netherlands; Pakistan; Philippines; Poland; Singapore; South Africa; South Korea; Spain; Taiwan; Thailand; Turkey; UAE; Ukraine; United Kingdom; and Vietnam; with additional agents and partners worldwide.

Meet Jim Berlin (Founder & CEO)

After a 20-year career in the less-than-truckload (LTL) industry, most of that time spent at TNT/USF Red Star, Jim founded Logistics Plus in 1996 with only three employees, one customer, and a $120,000 purchase order. Though he is a New York City native, Jim has invested heavily in the community’s economic development since relocating to Erie, PA. In 2003, he renovated the 80-year-old former train station and made it the company’s global headquarters, and he actively participates in many civic initiatives. In addition to many company awards, Jim has been honored as a Most Admired CEO by the Manufacturer and Business Association (MBA), and Ernst & Young (EY) recognized Jim as Western Pennsylvania’s “Entrepreneur of the Year” in 2004. In 2005 he was named to the lifelong EY Entrepreneur of the Year World Hall of Fame. In addition to his company and community activities, Jim is also a member of the Business Advisory Council for the Federal Reserve Bank of Cleveland.

Meet Yuriy Ostapyak (COO)

Yuriy has over 19 years of experience in the international and domestic transportation, logistics, and supply chain sectors. Yuriy’s responsibilities include roles in Sales and Management, Trucking and Warehousing, Freight Forwarding and Third-Party Logistics, and Global Procurement. Yuriy has played a key role in closing complex acquisitions, negotiating terms, financial conditions, and third-party financing. He has established global FX structure and Global Reconciliation/Netting structures worldwide. He has a consistent track record of delivering positive results to complex customers and business units by identifying and resolving complex issues that reduce cost, uncover waste, and drive profitability and effectiveness. Yuriy earned his B.A. in International Business and Marketing from Edinboro University of Pennsylvania in 2004 and, subsequently, a Masters of International Economics from the Kyiv National Economic University.
